
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code uses the [insert-after] slot to insert a new node after a specified node in a node collection. It targets the node named "chapter1" within the "book" node's children and inserts a new node named "chapter2" with the value "Next book chapter" immediately after it. 
 * 
 * 1. [insert-after] - Inserts nodes after the specified node(s) in the expression.
 * 2. [x:@.book/*/chapter1] - Expression pointing to the "chapter1" node within the "book" node's children.
 * 3. [.] - Indicates the start of the nodes to be inserted.
 * 4. [chapter2:Next book chapter] - The new node to be inserted, with "chapter2" as its name and "Next book chapter" as its value.
 */
insert-after:x:@.book/*/chapter1
   .
      chapter2:Next book chapter
